canonical_structure.name: UBX-RXM-SPARTN
canonical_structure.description: SPARTN input status. This message shows info on a received SPARTN input message. It is output upon successful parsing of a SPARTN input message, irrespective of whether the SPARTN message is supported or not by the receiver. This message is deprecated. Use UBX-RXM-COR instead.

bits.name: msgUsed
bits.description: 2 = SPARTN message used successfully by the receiver, 1 = not used, 0 = do not know

issues: Defines the bytes at offset 4-7 as a single 4-byte reserved block rather than identifying the msgType field at offset 6.

valid_variations.reason: This variant represents documentation that treats the final 4 bytes of the message as an opaque reserved block, common in earlier firmware versions or specific product lines before the msgType field was explicitly identified.

adjudication.reasoning: All extractions agree on the class ID (0x02), message ID (0x33), and total payload length (8 bytes). They also agree on the first three fields (version, flags, subType). The discrepancy lies in the interpretation of the final 4 bytes. Extractions 1 and 3 provide a more granular mapping, identifying a 'msgType' field at offset 6, while extractions 2, 4, and 5 define those 4 bytes as a single reserved U4 field. Extraction 3 is the most complete as it includes the deprecation warning associated with newer firmware (LAP 1.50).
